cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as object tracking and segmentation using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new baseline method that uses a single convolutional network, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the evaluation metrics for multi-object tracking, which can be considered as a machine learning (cs.LG) problem. The proposed method involves tracking objects in videos, which can be categorized under robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with dense pixel-level annotations, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
